The paper deals with the problem of allocating impressions to sellers in e-commerce websites, which involves designing efficient algorithms that take into account the strategic behavior of the sellers. This problem falls under the domain of game theory and mechanism design, which are covered by the cs.GT and cs.EC sub-categories. The paper also employs deep reinforcement learning to design the algorithms, which is covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of revenue maximization in e-commerce, which is related to information retrieval and recommendation systems, covered by the cs.IR sub-category.
